Scheduling Services<assessment@swin.edu.au>
​
MAXWELL MORRISSY​
​
accessability​
Dear Maxwell,

You are receiving this email because you have Equitable Assessment Arrangements (EAA) for your Semester 2 2025 exams.
 
Your attached Exam Timetable states all of your equitable assessment arrangements for your exams including:
•       Exam date/s
•       Amended start times
•       Breaks permitted
•       Any additional requirements
•       Maximum finish time - You are permitted to leave earlier should you finish the exam prior to your adjusted maximum finish time
Please note that you must be available for exams for the entire examination period.
 
Important: For all online assessments, please refer to Canvas or contact your Unit Convenor.
The Exam Timetable attached is your timetable for invigilated/on-campus exams only. For invigilated assessments, all EAA students must rely solely on your timetable attached to this email. The timetable within the Exam Summary and My Calendar through My Swinburne does not reflect your equitable assessment arrangements. You will not get your seat number before the exam. Your seat number will be allocated on arrival on the exam day.
 
Please note your exam timetable may be subject to change. If this is necessary, we will notify you immediately.
 
Arrival:
You must arrive at least 15 minutes before the exam start time.
 
Exam office details:
BA Building, Room BA507 on Hawthorn Campus Hawthorn Campus Map - http://www.swinburne.edu.au/contacts-campuses/campuses/hawthorn/documents/hawthorn.pdf
 
If you have any issues or queries relating to your EAA arrangements, please contact the Access Ability team via email accessability@swin.edu.au
 
Any other queries related to exam timetabling should be directed to assessment@swin.edu.au
 
Yours sincerely,
 
Scheduling Services
